            </div>
              <div class="card-product-infos">
              <h2>Cotton</h2>
                 <p>Cotton is extremely versatile, but only 30% is rainwater-grown, the rest requires irrigation <strong>(10,000-20,000 gallons per jeans, and ~ 3,000 per T-shirt!)</strong> <%= link_to '(link)', "https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/fashion/fabrics-environment-fast-fashion-eco-friendly-pollution-waste-polyester-cotton-fur-recycle-a8963921.html", :target => "_blank" %>, causing environmental disasters like the Aral Sea shrinkage <%= link_to "(link)", "https://www.theguardian.com/sustainable-business/sustainable-fashion-blog/2014/oct/01/cotton-production-linked-to-images-of-the-dried-up-aral-sea-basin", :target => "_blank" %>. Production requires heavy <strong>use of pesticides and chemicals</strong>, and/or GM-crop, contributing to heavy debt linked to farmer suicides in India <%= link_to "(link)", "https://www.theguardian.com/global-development/gallery/2014/may/05/india-cotton-suicides-farmer-deaths-gm-seeds", :target => "_blank" %>. Long term cultivation causes erosion and depletes soil nutrients, resulting in further encroachment into habitats. In addition, most of the world's cotton is grown in developing countries where environmental laws are not heavily enforced. Read more about cotton's impact <%= link_to "here", "https://www.tortoiseandladygrey.com/2014/09/01/textile-review-the-environmental-impacts-of-cotton/", :target => "_blank" %> and <%= link_to "here", "https://www.worldwildlife.org/industries/cotton" %>.</p>
