              <h2>Wool/Cashmere/Alpaca/Mohair</h2>
              <p>Animal fibers like wool, cashmere, alpaca and mohair and angora are <strong>quite sustainable</strong> and don't involve killing of the animals. However, there has been reports <%= link_to "(link)", "https://investigations.peta.org/australian-wool-industry-cruelty/", :target => "_blank" %> by animal rights activists in Australia of shearers kicking, punching and killing the animals while shearing, as well as <strong>reports of animal cruelty</strong> in China, the largest producer of Angora wool from rabbits. Non-organic farming of animals may also involve anti-tick with harmful chemicals. Where possible, buy local or free-trade wool to avoid these issues. Kept carefully, woolen clothes will endure much longer than cotton garments.</p>
