              <p>Eiderdown is very expensive and hand-collected after being shed by eider geese. However most down comes from geese, and is a byproduct of livestock farming that would otherwise be thrown away. <strong>Ethical concerns come from the practice of live plucking</strong> <%= link_to "(link)", "https://www.theguardian.com/world/2016/jan/14/winter-coat-ethically-produced-down-goose-feathers", :target => "_blank" %>, which can be done several times a year until the goose is slaughtered. Live-plucking is banned in the U.S and some European countries, but still occurs in some Eastern European countries and China. The alternative is synthetic filling in your blankets, which we do not recommend either. Therefore, <strong>look for ethical real down, or recycled real down</strong> for a more sustainable choice.</p>
