                <p>We'll be the first to admit, leather looks awesome. But non-eco friendly leather results in: <strong>huge methane emissions</strong> (livestock are estimated to be responsible for 14.5% of global greenhouse gass emission) <%= link_to "(link)", "http://www.fao.org/news/story/en/item/197623/icode/", :target => "_blank" %>; <strong>deforestation</strong>; <strong>toxic chemicals</strong> from tanning (carcinogenic chromium, lead, arsenic and acids); polluted waterways. <strong>Tannery workers suffer from cancer, kidney and liver damage, and reproductive problems</strong>. Sustainable leather is a possibility, but leather alternatives derived from pineapples, grapes, mushrooms or seaweed are better!</p>
